'''Soul Blazer''' is an action role-playing video game developed by '''Quintet''' and published by '''Enix''' for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System. It is the first game in the "Soul Trilogy" (Soul Blazer → Illusion of Gaia → Terranigma).

==Overview==

The player controls a divine servant sent by The Master to defeat Deathtoll and restore the souls of inhabitants across six acts. Key features:
* Action RPG with real-time combat
* Soul Lair system - defeat monster spawners to release trapped souls
* NPCs provide items, hints, and story progression when released
* 8 swords, 8 armors, 8 magic spells
* Transformation abilities (Mole, Angel, Mouse, Mermaid)

